German[edit]

Etymology[edit]

From aus- (“out”) +‎ füllen (“to fill”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /ˈaʊ̯sˌfʏlən/, [ˈʔäo̯sˌfʏlən], [-ˌfʏl̩n]
  • Audio (Austria)
    		(file)
  • Hyphenation: aus‧fül‧len

Verb[edit]

ausfüllen (third-person singular simple present füllt aus, past tense füllte aus, past participle ausgefüllt, auxiliary haben)

  1. to fill in; to fill completely; to take up
  2. to fill in (UK); to fill out (US) (a form)
  3. to fill; to fulfil; to live up to (a position, task)
  4. to fulfil; to satisfy (someone, e.g. of a job)
